    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S, featuring the legendary 3.6L flat-six powerplant mated to a crisp 6-speed manual transaxle. This widebody 996.2 variant delivers exceptional lateral grip via its factory-tuned AWD system and remains composed under load thanks to its precision-engineered suspension geometry. Key preventative maintenance has been prioritized, including a documented dual-row ceramic IMS bearing retrofit and a full cooling system overhaul (water pump, low-temp thermostat, and flushed radiators). The braking system retains its bite with ventilated rotors and four-piston monobloc calipers. While the exterior displays minor stone chips indicative of its use as a driver's tool, the engine exhibits perfect compression across all cylinders and a leak-free undercarriage. This is an honest, high-performance example ready for the track or the canyon roads.",
      "price": 36500.0,
